  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accountant",
  "description": "<p><u>Responsibilities</u></p><ol><li>Responsible for full set of accounts - day to day accounting operations, perform general ledger, AP, AR, and bank reconciliation</li><li>Responsible for preparation and closing of monthly and annual financial statements (including XBRL)</li><li>Responsible for employee payroll including CPF submission & employee income tax submission (IR8A etc)</li><li>Ensure timely and accurate financial reporting to Management</li><li>Support forecasting and budgeting exercise to Management</li><li>Preparation and submission of corporate tax</li><li>Responsible for statutory reporting, ensure compliance with all statutory and tax filing requirements</li><li>Coordinate and liaise with external parties like external auditors, tax agents, corporate secretarial agents, tax and government authorities where required</li><li>Support related companies’ financial closing and reporting</li><li>Perform any other duties as assigned</li></ol><p></p><p><u>Requirements</u></p><ol><li>Minimum Diploma holder in Accountancy</li><li>At least 3-5 years of accounting experience, preferably in commodities trading industry</li><li>Good knowledge in Financial Reporting Standards and Corporate Tax</li><li>Able to handle full set of accounting and statutory reporting</li><li>Well-versed in MS Office, especially MS Excel, PowerPoint and Word</li><li>Good communication skills in English (written & verbal)</li><li>Proactive and accountable, able to work independently, maintain accuracy and deliver to deadlines</li><li>Meticulous and well-organised</li><li>Positive attitude, driven and passionate about work</li></ol><p>Remuneration package commensurate with qualifications and experiences.</p>",
